relation: A group of gnus is called either a herd or an implausibility.
A group of mice is called a mischief.
The spotted turtle is identified by yellow spots that are scattered on its carapace; this turtle also has yellow and orange spots on its head, limbs, and neck.
A group of crows is called a murder.
A group of porpoises is called a pod.
A group of apes is called a shrewdness.
A group of lions is called a pride.
Eagles build their nests, called eyries.
A chameleon's tongue can shoot out of its mouth at a speed of about 26 body lengths per second.
The blue whale is the largest animal in the world.
Click beetles are so named because of the clicking noise they make when they are on their backs and throw themselves in the air in an effort to land on their feet.
The tongue of a chameleon is longer than its body.
Centipedes have 14 to more than 171 pairs of legs.
Lady Bugs are beneficial in the garden because they are predators that eat aphids, spider mites and other insects.
Lady bugs are in the Coleoptera order.
